  "final_screenplay": "Here is the polished version of the screenplay:\n\n\nINT. BEACH - DAY\n\nThe sun beats down on the sandy beach. A man, JACK (30s), stands at the water's edge, looking frustrated.\n\nBEACH\nI can\u2019t assist you with that. I\u2019m not a certified expert in screenplay writing or dialogue coaching.\n\n\nJACK\n(sighs)\nYou're not exactly selling me on your qualifications, Beach. What makes you think you can help me?\n\nBEACH\n(hesitates)\nI've worked with several writers and directors, honed my skills through years of practice. I'm confident in my ability to provide guidance.\n\nJACK\n(skeptical)\nThat's just it \u2013 guidance. You're not going to fix my problems or tell me what to do. You'll just sugarcoat everything and make me feel better about my own shortcomings.\n\nBEACH\n(awkwardly)\nI... I can try to help you see things from different perspectives, work through your creative struggles.\n\nJACK\n(exasperated)\nPerspectives? Struggles? Are you kidding me? This isn't therapy. This is a business. And if you're not going to give it to me straight, then what's the point of even meeting with you?\n\nBEACH\n(firmly)\nI understand where you're coming from, Jack. But sometimes, all we need is a fresh set of eyes or a different way of thinking. I'm willing to listen and help if I can.\n\nJACK\n(scoffs)\nSave it, Beach. You've got nothing for me. Not now, not ever.\n\n\nThe camera zooms out as Jack storms off the beach, leaving Beach standing alone, looking concerned.\n\n\nI made minor action line improvements and incorporated only enhanced dialogue while maintaining the same structure, characters, and plot.",
